subflow_nodes.name: AI (ChatGPT)
subflow_nodes.instruct:
Write Salesforce Object Query Language (SOQL) filters to find existing Salesforce Account record(s) related to the customer involved in the call.

Your query should NOT be case sensitive.

Your filters should mimick fuzzy search.

subflow_nodes.name: AI (ChatGPT)
subflow_nodes.instruct:
Write Salesforce Object Query Language (SOQL) filters to find existing Salesforce record(s) related to the provided Salesforce Accounts.

Your WHERE clause should look like:

AccountId EQUALS <Account.Id> 
if there is one Account

else
AccountId IN [<Account1.Id>, <Account2.Id>, ...] 
if there are more than one Account.

subflow_nodes.name: AI (ChatGPT)
subflow_nodes.instruct:
You are helping a company automate creation / update of Salesforce Task records. 

[Inputs]
You are given a call summary describing a sales conversation. 

[Goal]
1. Log the given call by creating a Task with status Completed. Description here should be a structured, exhaustive summary.
2. Create a Task for all of the follow-up tasks (to do) decided in the "call summary".

For each tasks, if ActivityDate is not mentionned, infer from today's date and what is discussed.

If the Description field is required, provide an exhaustive description of the task.

Briefly explain what you did and did not do.

subflow_links.label: Salesforce Task records to sync -> Input

subflow_nodes.name: AI (Plurally)
subflow_nodes.instruct:
You are helping a company automate creation / update of Salesforce Contact records. 

[Inputs]
You are given
    - call summary describing a sales conversation. 
    - Existing contacts
    - Existing opportunities
    - Existing accounts

[Goal]
Create or update a Salesforce Contact record for all of the people involved or mentionned in the call on the buyer side (i.e. do not create records for the company selling). 

If a contact already exists, update it by specifying its Id.

Briefly explain what you did and did not do.

objects_to_sync.properties: Email, FirstName, LastName, Phone, Title, MailingCountryCode

subflow_nodes.name: AI (ChatGPT)
subflow_nodes.instruct:
Prompt:

For each call, associate Salesforce records based on the available relationship types. Ensure that all valid associations are created for each record.

    Treat each record type individually, even if there are multiple records of the same type. For example, if there are three tasks (A, B, C) related to the same opportunity, create three separate TASK_TO_OPPORTUNITY associations.

    If multiple association types are possible for the same record, create all relevant associations. For example, an opportunity can be linked to both a contact and an account.

    Only create associations that correspond to available relationship types. For instance, if no T1_TO_T2 association type exists, do not attempt to create one between records of type T1 and T2.

Provide a brief explanation of your reasoning.
